{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nThe original premise (promote a bash credential helper, wire a dispatcher arm, add `.rebar/config.conf` + `read-config.sh`) is OBSOLETE after the bash->Python migration. Config PERSISTENCE + reconciler-READ are already solved: `resolve_jira_settings` (`src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/acli_subprocess.py`) resolves url/user/project through `load_config().jira.*` (typed `JiraConfig`, reading `rebar.toml [tool.rebar.jira]` and legacy `.rebar/config.conf`), with `JIRA_URL/USER/PROJECT` env overriding and `JIRA_API_TOKEN` env-only; `rebar bridge-probe` already validates credentials end-to-end; c8cc shipped client-setup docs. The ONLY genuinely-missing piece is an INTERACTIVE onboarding UX — today you must hand-set env / hand-edit config then run `rebar bridge-probe`.\n\n## What\nAdd an interactive `rebar jira-onboard` subcommand that detects existing Jira settings, prompts for what's missing, validates them, and persists to the EXISTING typed config (no new config layer). Mirror the existing `rebar llm setup` wizard precedent (`src/rebar/_cli/_llm_commands.py`).\n\n## Scope\n- New `rebar jira-onboard` CLI subcommand (Python, in `src/rebar/_cli/`): detect JIRA_URL/USER/PROJECT/API_TOKEN, prompt for missing url/user/project, write them to `[tool.rebar.jira]` (or `.rebar/config.conf`); guide the user that `JIRA_API_TOKEN` stays an env secret (do NOT persist the token to a file).\n- Reuse `bridge-probe`'s validation as the post-onboard end-to-end check.\n- Out: any new config layer, persisting secrets to disk, touching the reconciler's read path (already done).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `rebar jira-onboard` interactive subcommand: detects existing settings, prompts for missing url/user/project, validates (reuse/invoke bridge-probe), and persists url/user/project to the existing typed config ([tool.rebar.jira] / .rebar/config.conf).\n- [ ] `JIRA_API_TOKEN` is treated as an env-only secret (guidance shown; never written to a config file); reuses `resolve_jira_settings`/`load_config().jira` (no new config layer).\n- [ ] Documented (CLI help text + docs) and reachable via the `rebar` CLI.\n- [ ] Tests cover detect + persist + the env-only-token rule; full suite green.","title":"Add interactive 'rebar jira-onboard' wizard (config persistence + reconciler-read already done)"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782780883360427001,"uuid":"10ab2608-e4e8-4cc8-913d-b99d0b9c876d"}